  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Adult Curriculum The Quantum style is a unique blend of Tae Kwon Do , Wing Chun, Judo , and Arnis , among other styles, with a focus on self-actualization, total body healing, and strength. New students and beginners are always welcome, and your first week of classes is free! Once enrolled, new students are asked to come to class at least two times a week to cultivate their training practice.  Intermediate students are encouraged to attend two to three times a week, and advanced students three to four. We currently offer online and limited in-person martial arts classes for adults seven days a week. Check out our class schedule for more information about our current class offerings! Promotions Every six to eight weeks, there is a belt test to determine who is ready to move on to the next level.  In order to participate in testings, students must ask permission from the Instructor within the week preceding the test. Testings typically happen on Saturdays and Mondays, and begin with an in-depth community cleaning of the Dojo. Quantum Belts Click below on the belt you are currently wearing to find information about what you need to know for your next test. White Belt (10th and 9th gup) Yellow Belt (8th and 7th gup) Green Belt (6th and 5th gup) Blue Belt (4th and 3rd gup) Red Belt (2nd and 1st gup) Black Belt (1st to 3rd dan) — check with your instructor Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
